<SECOND>PM-BRF--Boy Saved,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Firefighter Pulls Boy From Manhole</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 8-year-old boy plunged 10 feet to his death
in a water-filled sewer when he stepped on a manhole covered only
with a piece of carpet, authorities said.
   Firefighters discovered Jesus Cortez in 8 feet of water beneath
the street in his Bronx neighborhood on Sunday, said John Mulligan,
a Fire Department spokesman.
   ``We were hoping with the cold water there would be a better
chance of reviving him,'' said fire department diver Richard Evers,
42.
   Children who had been playing with the boy prior to the accident
told firefighters the manhole was covered with a piece of carpet,
said Lt. Joseph Berry.
   There was no immediate comment from city officials on whether
the manhold was covered.
</TEXT>
