<TEXT>
   Soldiers in the Swiss army will
receive two pairs of gloves for emergency situations to prevent the
spread of AIDS, according to a military magazine.
   The gloves will form part of each soldier's first aid kit and
are intended to prevent contact with blood infected with the AIDS
virus, the Schweizerische Militaerzeitschrift magazine reported.
   Switzerland has the highest per capita AIDS rate in Europe, with
5.4 cases per 100,000.
