<HEAD>Five Boys Charged With Killing Classmate for About 15 Cents</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five boys were charged with killing a
9-year-old classmate who refused to give them his pocket money,
police said Monday.
   The youths grabbed Suh Kwang-chan outside his school in rural
Kohung on Friday and demanded he give them the equivalent of 15
cents, police said. When Suh refused, they tied his hands, took him
to a mountain, beat him with bamboo sticks and buried him alive,
police said.
   Suh died of suffocation and his body was found by a villager,
police said.
   The names of the accused were withheld and police said they
would be dealt with in juvenile courts.
   Newspapers quoted Suh's mother, Shin Dong-shim, as saying her
son had been afraid to go to school because of bullying from other
children. She said Suh complained his classmates had tried to force
him to hand over pocket money or steal, news reports said.
