<SECOND>AM-Bush-Jogging,100</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bush Goes Jogging in Rain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush went jogging Monday in a light
rain that turned into a downpour. He kept on running, exclaiming,
``We're going swimming.''
   Accompanied by Republican Party chief Lee Atwater and a small
entourage, Bush jogged for 28 minutes around Hains Point in East
Potomac Park. A police boat followed along in the choppy river
waters.
   There was a light drizzle when Bush started and it turned into a
heavy rain. By the time Bush stopped, the rain had tapered off
again.
   Returning to the White House in his limousine with soaked shoes
and socks, Bush took his running mates to the pool house for dry
clothes. Then he headed for the sauna.
