<HEAD>Lone Survivor Headed For Recovery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DAHLONEGA, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 14-year-old girl was headed for a full
recovery Monday after surviving 15 hours on a north Georgia
mountain near the bodies of four relatives and the wreckage of
their plane.
   Evelyn Michelle Ward of Griffin was in stable condition with an
excellent prognosis, said Sister Frances Ann of St. Joseph's
Hospital in Dahlonega. She had a broken arm, cuts, scrapes and
burns.
   She was injured when her family's single-engine Beechcraft
crashed Saturday, authorities said. Among those killed were her
mother and stepfather.
   Searchers began looking for the plane, which was bound from
Griffin to Dahlonega, after an automatic distress signal was picked
up.
