<HEAD>Sisterhood Wins First Liechtenstein Prize</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VADUZ, Liechtenstein (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Caritas Socialis, a Vienna-based
Christian sisterhood committed to protecting the family, won the
first $60,600 Prince Franz Josef of Liechtenstein Prize, sponsors
announced Monday.
   The prize was initiated by the Prince of Liechtenstein
Foundation last year to mark the 50th anniversary of the prince's
reign.
   The sisterhood, founded in 1883, does charitable work in
German-language regions, Brazil and Israeli-occupied territory.
   The foundation said the group's activities range from ``a
commitment to protect unborn life to a commitment to having people
die in dignity close to their family.''
