<FIRST>r a AM-Poll-Method 1stLd-Writethru a0605 05-01 0714</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Poll-Method, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0605,0733</SECOND>
<HEAD>Poll on Communism Reached 1,108 Nationwide</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 2nd graf to delete extraneous word.</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Poll-Communism</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   This Media General-Associated Press poll is
based on telephone interviews March 6-15 with 1,108 adults in the
continental United States. Phone numbers were selected randomly and
interviews were conducted with the adult who had the most recent
birthday, a random phenomenon.
   The results were weighted to adjust for variations in the
sample. The poll has a 3-point margin of error, meaning that if
every adult American were asked the same questions, the results
theoretically would be within 3 points of the poll's results, 19
times out of 20. The error margin is larger for subgroups.
   There are other sources of potential error in polls, including
the wording and order of questions. These are the questions in this
poll; because of rounding, sums may not total 100:
   1. Overall, do you think communism is on the rise around the
world, on the decline, or is it holding steady? Rise: 27 percent.
Decline: 19 percent. Steady: 46 percent. Don't know or no answer: 8.
   2. How about capitalism _ do you think it is on the rise around
the world, on the decline, or is it holding steady? Rise: 37.
Decline: 9. Steady: 44. DK-NA: 10.
   3. Which do you think has more influence in the world right now,
capitalism or communism? Capitalism: 62. Communism: 23. DK-NA: 14.
   4. Do you think most communist countries follow the Soviet
Union's policies as much now as they did in the past? Yes: 20. No:
70. DK-NA: 10.
   5. Do you think communism in .... is becoming more of a threat
to the security of the United States than it has been in the past,
less of a threat, is it about the same, or has it never been a
threat?
   a. Latin America. More: 44. Less: 7. Same: 30. Never: 9. DK-NA:
10.
   b. the Soviet Union. More: 14. Less: 38. Same: 37. Never: 2.
DK-NA: 9.
   c. China: More: 14. Less: 34. Same: 32. Never: 6. DK-NA: 13.
   d. Eastern Europe: More: 15. Less: 28. Same: 35. Never: 7.
DK-NA: 16.
   6. Do you think closer relations between China and the Soviet
Union would be a threat to the United States? Yes: 49. No: 41.
DK-NA: 10.
   7. Generally, do you think most communist nations nowadays are
giving their people more freedom, or not? Yes: 67. No: 24. DK-NA: 9.
   8a. Thinking about the communist economic system _ with the
government controlling most industry and business _ do you think
the Soviet Union is moving away from the communist economic system,
or not? Yes: 58. No: 28. DK-NA: 13.
   b. How about some of the Eastern European countries _ do you
think they are moving away from the communist economic system, or
not? Yes: 47. No: 27. DK-NA: 25.
   c. How about China _ is it moving away from the communist
economic system, or not? Yes: 45. No: 30. DK-NA: 24.
   9a. Now think about the communist political system, with one
party sponsoring candidates for office _ do you think the Soviet
Union is moving away from that political system, or not? Yes: 31.
No: 47. DK-NA: 22.
   b. How about some of the Eastern European countries _ are they
moving away from the communist political system, or not? Yes: 32.
No: 39. DK-NA: 29.
   c. How about China _ is it moving away from the communist
political system, or not? Yes: 23. No: 49. DK-NA: 28.
   10. Some people say that if the United States increased its
trade with the Soviet Union, that would encourage democratic
reforms there. Others say it would only keep the current communist
system going. Which do you think is right _ would more U.S. trade
encourage democratic reform, or keep the current communist system
going? Reform: 49. Keep going: 33. DK-NA: 18.
   11. Which of these do you think is the greatest problem with
communism: no free speech, lack of religious freedom, no profit
motive, only one political party, or lack of consumer goods?
Speech: 29. Religious freedom: 17. Profit motive: 14. One party:
22. Consumer goods: 11. DK-NA: 8.
   12. In your view, is communism dying, or not? Yes: 25. No: 67.
DK-NA: 8.
</TEXT>
