cents a pound; feeder cattle were .22 cent lower to .25 cent higher
with May at 76.30 cents a pound; hogs were .03 cent to .18 cent
higher with June at 46.65 cents a pound; frozen pork bellies were
.35 cent lower to .10 cent higher with May at 31.05 cents a pound.
   Livestock futures settled higher Friday, while pork futures were
lower.
