<FIRST>r f AM-HeilemanReorganization     05-01 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Heileman Reorganization,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>Heileman Announces Reorganization Into Four Divisions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LA CROSSE, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   G. Heileman Brewing Co. is being
reorganized into four distinct divisions, a move a company
spokesmen said Monday will allow the brewery to capitalize on its
regional strengths.
   The reorganization is based on geography, with the four
divisions being East, Midwest, Texas and West. The divisional
presidents will report to Murray Cutbush, president and chief
operating officer of Heileman, who will remain in La Crosse.
   Cutbush said the brewery's new structure ``will allow the
company to further develop and intensify the strategy that has made
the G. Heileman Brewing Co. the nation's premiere regional brewer.''
   Cutbush added: ``Our involvement with the local community and
our local network of wholesalers in each region will be increased.
This certainly strengthens our position entering the peak summer
selling season and will enable us to aggressively pursue regional
marketing and sales opportunities.''
</TEXT>
