<FIRST>r f AM-BoeingSale     05-01 0112</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Boeing Sale,0116</SECOND>
<HEAD>Air Algerie Orders Three 767s</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Air Algerie has ordered three Boeing 767-300
jetliners for about $264 million, including spare parts and
training, Boeing Commercial Airplanes officials said Monday.
   The planes, each seating 253 passengers in two classes or 264 in
all-economy seating, are for delivery in April, June and August
next year, a Boeing statement said.
   The order by the national airline of Algeria boosts the total
for the 767 to 421 planes from 41 customers. Total orders received
by Boeing for all commercial jets this year stand at 517 planes and
$28 billion, compared with 636 planes and $29.7 billion for all of
1988.
